<br>
Horses are in the game, if you need to get somewhere, rent a horse from a friendly stablemaster for a few silver.<br>
<br>
Many classes have SoW type speed buffs available to them.<br>
<br>
Also, NPC's are available for almost anything you need in the game, including enchanter steel for magical armor/weaponsmithing etc.  The game seems to have a balance of PC and NPC interaction, to not FORCE you to sit around asking for a teleport for 2 hours from a greedy DrOoD that wants 1000pp for a teleport.<br>
<br>
Personally, I love the pet classes in DAoC.  Pets are stronger than in EQ, have way less agro on area mobs, keep mobs off the caster, and you can buff/heal your pets.  In addition, some pet classes can summon Tank-Cleric pets, that will actually stop fighting, and start healing you or your group members during big fights.<br>
<br>
My pet is so good, I send him off to kill a blue mob (which he can usually solo), while I nuke and melee a high blue mob.  Usually, we both finish at the same time, giving double experiance.  Picture a Enchanter in DAoC, basically, it is a Magician/Enchanter Combo in EQ + you can heal pet.  So you can keep mobs mezzed/stuned, send off pet on another mob, and basically kick some azz.<br>
<br>
Of course, other classes are awesome to.  I personally love Champions/Thanes (Paladins on crack), and  Shamans, as well as Bards are damn good (Bigtime tank w/songs in DAoC).<br>
<br>
Lotsa choices, do some research, try different ones, and see what you like.<br>
<br>
