<br>
Druids and other classes get pets too - druids can summon trees to come help them, or summon strong animals from the forests to aid them.  Enchanters can summon a full warrior of nearly equal level to their own.  Spiritmasters can summon dead super-tanks or dead tank-clerics to help them. Etc.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying they are the best classes in the game.  All I am saying is that pet classes in DAoC I find to be incredibly fun to play and not nerfed or handicapped in anyway.<br>
<br>
I recommend you try many classes, to see what suits you.  I am a big caster fan in all games really, but hybrids are a second favorite. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uxuilidar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xuilidar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(10/7/01 12:05:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What are the wizards err taxis of Daoc</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What are the wizards err taxis of Daoc<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
